# Extension output (created when you run "Set up" in the Dev Host)
**/.tools/
**/.vscode/

# Resolved dependency state. The committed go.mod files are minimal (tool
# directives only); the extension only reads that text. Actually *running* a tool
# — especially golangci-lint — pulls its full dependency tree into go.sum (and
# bloats go.mod with hundreds of indirect requires). That's local, throwaway
# state for Level-2 testing only; never commit it. Run ./setup.sh to regenerate.
**/go.sum
